briefdescription.para: Compute the number of bits required to store the given number of values.

detaileddescription.para: Note that the computed result for a number smaller or equal to zero is undefined. The input number can be any compile-time constant.

briefdescription.para: Compute the number of bits required to store the given number of (signed) enum values.

simplesect.para: This is intended to be used when storing enum values in a bitfield without casting the enum type to an unsigned integer. (At least GCC considers enums to be signed and hence wastes one bit when all enumerants are non-negative).
